info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 10:29PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF CENTRAL ST. LOUIS AND SOUTHERN LAKE COUNTIES THROUGH 1100 PM CDT... At 1029 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms located 11 miles north of Mountain Iron and near Embarrass, moving southeast at 40 mph. HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow unsecured objects around. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible. Locations impacted include... Virginia, Mountain Iron, Hoyt Lakes, Silver Bay, Gilbert, Aurora, Babbitt, Biwabik, Embarrass, Tower, Fairbanks, Wolf Lake, Brimson, Whyte, Thomas Lake Near Brimson, Finland, Highland Lake, Birch Lake, Whiteface Reservoir, and Franklin. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH
info.instruction: Anyone outdoors, including anyone on or in the water, should seek shelter inside a sturdy building or hard topped vehicle.
